com.vector.cfg.gen.core.genusage.groovy.api

Interface IGenerationSettingsApi


  • @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
 @PublishedApiDomain(value=AUTOMATION_IF)
public interface IGenerationSettingsApi

    Settings

    This class encapsulates all settings which belong to a generation process.
    E.g.
    • Select the generators to execute
    • Select the target type
    • Select the external generation steps
    • If the module supports multiple module configurations, select the configurations which shall be generated

    (c) Copyright Vctr Informatik GmbH. All Rights Reserved.

      • selectGeneratorByDefRef

        @PublishedMethod
void selectGeneratorByDefRef(DefRef defRef)
        This method fetches the generators associated with the passed DefRef and adds them to the list of generators which shall be executed.
        It is possible to pass a full qualified DefRef (E.g. "/MICROSAR/Adc") or only the module definition short name of the DefRef (E.g. "Os").
        Passed MSN are interpreted to match any package ("/[ANY]/MSN").
        Already selected generators are not removed by this method.
        If a DefRef could not be resolved to a generator, a GeneratorNotFoundException will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        generators - String of defRef or module definition short name
        Throws:
        GeneratorNotFoundException
